skin_func <- function(){
  gender <- readline(prompt ="  ) F, M: ")
  age <- readline(prompt ="  ) 20, 30, 40: ")
  job <- readline(prompt ="   ) YES, NO: ")
  marry <- readline(prompt ="   ) YES, NO: ")
  car <- readline(prompt ="    ) YES, NO: ")
 
  #  
  library(C50)

  skin <- read.csv("C:/data/skin.csv", header = T)
  skin <- skin[ ,-1]
  
  #  
  skin$gender <- ifelse(skin$gender == "", "M", "F")
  skin$age <- factor(gsub('','', as.character(skin$age)))
  
  #  1_set.seed()
  set.seed(11)
  skin_shuffle <- skin[sample(nrow(skin)),]
  
  
  train_num <- round(0.7*nrow(skin_shuffle),0)
  skin_train <- skin_shuffle[1:train_num, ]
  skin_test <- skin_shuffle[(train_num +1): nrow(skin_shuffle), ]
  
  
                  #  2_trials:laplace 
  skin_model <- C5.0(skin_train[ ,-6], skin_train[ ,6], trials = 10)
  
  # 1. data .
  
  cust_data1 <- data.frame(gender = toupper(gender), age = as.numeric(age), job = toupper(job),
                            marry = toupper(marry), car = toupper(car))

  # 2.   .
  skin_result <- predict(skin_model, cust_data1)
  print(paste(" ", skin_result," .")) 
  
  library(gmodels)
  skin_result <- predict(skin_model, skin_test[ ,-6])
  CrossTable(x = skin_test[,6], y=skin_result)
}

decision_fun <- function(){
  rm()
  print(" csv  ")
  data <- file.choose()
  na.string <- NA
  #  factor ....
  table1 <- read.csv(data, header = T, na.string = na.string)
  
  d_col <- menu(c(colnames(table1),'non'), title="   ")

  table1 <- table1[,-d_col]

  l_col <- menu(colnames(table1), title="label    ")
  trials <- readline(prompt = "trials   ")
 
  #  
  library(C50)
  library(gmodels)
  library(rpart)
  library(rattle)

  
  #  1_set.seed()
  set.seed(11)
  table_shuffle <- table1[sample(nrow(table1)),]
  
  
  train_num <- round(0.7*nrow(table_shuffle),0)
  table_train <- table_shuffle[1:train_num, ]
  table_test <- table_shuffle[(train_num +1): nrow(table_shuffle), ]
  
  l_col <-  colnames(table1)[l_col]
  ncol1 <- which(colnames(table1) == l_col)
          
  #  2_trials:laplace 
  model <- C5.0(table_train[ ,-ncol1], table_train[ ,ncol1], trials = as.numeric(trials))
  result <- predict(model, table_test[ ,-ncol1])
  
  CrossTable(x = table_test[,ncol1], y= result)
  
  # as.formula paste ~. .
  tree <- rpart(label~. , data=data.frame(table1[,-ncol1], label = table1[,l_col]),
                control=rpart.control(minsplit=2))
  fancyRpartPlot(tree,palettes = c("Greys","RdPu"))
}
